git-crypt (0.5.0-1~1.gbp214e2f) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  ** SNAPSHOT build @214e2febf9e0e3c91a4ac585b5a3829a5d10aad6 **

  [ Andrew Ayer ]
  * Remove gnuism from Makefile
  * Mark .gpg files in .git-crypt as binary
  * Don't hard code path to git-crypt in .git/config on Linux

  [ Aaron Heimlich ]
  * More flexible gpg invocation. git-crypt will now use the value of the "gpg.program" git configuration setting. If "gpg.program" is not set, then it will fall back to the previous behavior of using "gpg".

  [ Andrew Ayer ]

